    <abstract>
      <p><bold>Summary:</bold> We present rCGH, a comprehensive array-based comparative genomic hybridization analysis workflow, integrating computational improvements and functionalities specifically designed for precision medicine. rCGH supports the major microarray platforms, ensures a full traceability and facilitates profiles interpretation and decision-making through sharable interactive visualizations.</p>
      <p><bold>Availability and implementation:</bold> The rCGH R package is available on bioconductor (under Artistic-2.0). The aCGH-viewer is available at <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://fredcommo.shinyapps.io/aCGH&amp;lowbar;viewer">https://fredcommo.shinyapps.io/aCGH_viewer</ext-link>, and the application implementation is freely available for installation at <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/fredcommo/aCGH&amp;lowbar;viewer">https://github.com/fredcommo/aCGH_viewer</ext-link>.</p>
      <p>
        <bold>Contact:</bold>
        <email>frederic.commo@gustaveroussy.fr</email>
      </p>
